    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's a good start. But some people argue that the whole idea of \"substantive\" due process is actually pretty dangerous because it lets judges basically make up new rights that aren't explicitly in the Constitution. How should I address that criticism in my lesson so it doesn't sound like I'm just ignoring the validity of their concerns?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
